# AI Scope Lock (Hard Guardrail)

This repository is under strict scope control. The agent MUST follow all rules below.

## Allowed Scope (Only Two Workstreams)

1. Add/maintain `cmd_key` redundancy and consistency checks tied to `device_ownership`.
2. Add/maintain automated backup for `sentinel.db` to object storage.

Any change outside these two workstreams is out-of-scope unless user explicitly re-authorizes.

## Forbidden Changes

- MUST NOT change frontend/UI/CSS/dashboard routes/assets.
- MUST NOT change firmware files (including `Croc Sentinel.ino`).
- MUST NOT do unrelated modularization/refactors/cleanup.
- MUST NOT add dependencies unless directly required by the two allowed workstreams.
- MUST NOT perform destructive git operations.

## File Discipline (No File Stuffing)

- MUST NOT create new files/modules unless strictly necessary for the two allowed workstreams.
- When creating a file is unavoidable, MUST keep it minimal and localized.
- Prefer editing existing in-scope files over adding new files.

## No-Drift Behavior

- MUST preserve existing behavior outside the approved scope.
- MUST NOT do silent logic rewrites, opportunistic rewrites, or broad “improvements”.
- If a structural change is unavoidable, MUST explain: blocker, touched files, and why smaller edits are insufficient.

## Execution Protocol

- Before editing, MUST list target files and explain why each file is in-scope.
- After each completed part, MUST run smoke checks and debug/fix issues before moving on.
- Validation MUST focus on changed in-scope files and directly impacted paths.
- If any request conflicts with this rule, MUST stop and ask for explicit user approval.

